      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm working as a consultant for a firm that's currently facing a lot of pushback from their executive board regarding our new DEI initiatives. The leadership is very skeptical and they basically think these programs undermine meritocracy. I need to prepare for a heated meeting where I'll have to address their concerns. Can you help me by playing devil's advocate? I need you to build the strongest possible case against affirmative action and DEI programs—specifically the argument that a race-blind approach is the only way to ensure actual fairness and that these programs actually cause more division than they solve.",
